cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
1) cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with coded computing techniques for fault and straggler tolerance. 
2) cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper focuses on the numerical stability of polynomial based encoding methods. 
3) cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper discusses the trade-off between computation/communication and fault-tolerance. 
4) cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a numerically stable specialization of Lagrange coded computing. 
5) cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper uses orthogonal polynomials as a basis for constructing new codes for matrix multiplication.
